From: python-wasm build
Subject: Relax 3.12 configure's wasi host glob to accept wasm32-wasip2

3.12's configure has `*-*-wasi)` (exact match) where 3.13's has
`*-*-wasi*)` (glob). Because `host=wasm32-unknown-wasip2` ends in
`-wasip2`, not `-wasi`, 3.12 falls through to the catch-all and aborts
with "cross build not supported for wasm32-unknown-wasip2". 3.13 accepts
both wasm32-unknown-wasip1 and -wasip2 through the same glob.

This patch is the minimal forward port of 3.13's relaxation. configure
and configure.ac change identically.

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 89edc42..fdbb685 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -4280,7 +4280,7 @@ then
 	*-*-emscripten)
 	    ac_sys_system=Emscripten
 	    ;;
-	*-*-wasi)
+	*-*-wasi*)
 	    ac_sys_system=WASI
 	    ;;
 	*)
diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
index 1a02d19..e03023d 100644
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -556,7 +556,7 @@ then
 	*-*-emscripten)
 	    ac_sys_system=Emscripten
 	    ;;
-	*-*-wasi)
+	*-*-wasi*)
 	    ac_sys_system=WASI
 	    ;;
 	*)
